<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ENTRY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Re: "Merit Only" College Entry Proposal (Dec. 9): 
</P>
<P>
Notwithstanding the charts, tables, reports, studies and other hype presented 
in defense, the disproportionate number of outstanding Asian-Americans who have 
been turned away from certain California public universities and professional 
schools reinforces my belief that de facto discrimination in admissions 
practices is indeed going on in these institutions. 
</P>
<P>
The purpose of affirmative action is to help those minority students not 
proportionately represented on the campuses better their academic performance 
so they can gain admission to our institutions of higher learning. The intent 
is not to permit quotas to override other criteria. Asian-Americans value 
learning and are willing to work hard. America has much to gain if their 
pursuit of excellence is rewarded. The Bakke ruling reaffirmed merit as a 
determining criterion in judging admissibility to a UC medical school. The 
Olympic gold is awarded only for excellence. Rep. Dana Rohrabacher is to be 
complimented for his wisdom in sponsoring a congressional resolution which 
speaks to this inequity. The purpose of our institutions of higher learning is 
to pursue the truth. And excellence. 
</P>
<P>
U KYAW WIN 
</P>
<P>
Laguna Hills 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
