<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY ROUNDUP: CAL LUTHERAN LOSES 10TH IN ROW, 76-62 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Cal Lutheran's men's basketball team outshot Cal State Hayward, 51% to 36%, 
Monday night, but the Kingsmen were outrebounded, 46-24, in a 76-62 
nonconference loss at Hayward. The loss was the tenth in as many games for Cal 
Lutheran. 
</P>
<P>
Jeff deLaveaga scored a team-high 19 points for Cal Lutheran, and teammate Mike 
Demeter added 14 points and eight rebounds, but the Kingsmen were plagued by 26 
turnovers. 
</P>
<P>
In a women's college game: 
</P>
<P>
Valley 74, Pasadena City College 54 -- Valley jumped out to a 13-0 lead and 
cruised to the first-round win in the Candy Cane Classic in Riverside. 
</P>
<P>
Fourteen Valley players scored, led by Sandrine Rocher's 13 points and 
Christine Rumfola's 10 points. Valley improved to 9-2. Pasadena fell to 6-7. 
</P>
<P>
BOYS' BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
Chaminade 88, Cathedral 82 (OT) -- Charlie Fei tied the game in regulation with 
a layup after a steal, and Colin Havert went four for four from the free-throw 
line in overtime to seal a nonleague win at Chaminade. 
</P>
<P>
Mark Mirkovich scored a game-high 23 points and grabbed a team-high 10 rebounds 
for Chaminade (4-3), while Fei added 22 points. Cathedral fell to 6-3. 
</P>
<P>
Bishop Amat 61, Alemany 52 -- William Burr and Tim Fontenette scored 15 points 
each for Alemany (5-4) in a nonleague game at Bishop Amat. 
</P>
<P>
BOYS' SOCCER 
</P>
<P>
Channel Islands 3, St. Bonaventure 0 -- Goalkeeper Rosario Pina recorded his 
second shutout of the season to lead the Raiders (4-1-1) at St. Bonaventure. 
</P>
<P>
Harvard 6, La Jolla Country Day School 0 -- Andrew Weiss scored four goals for 
Harvard (5-1-1) in a nonleague match. 
</P>
