<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: BODY OF NEWBORN FOUND ON REMOTE ROAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The body of a newborn baby was found Monday beside a road in a remote area 
north of Castaic, the Los Angeles County Sheriff's Department reported. 
</P>
<P>
The body was discovered about 4:30 p.m. next to Lake Hughes Road, about two 
miles east of the Golden State Freeway, Deputy George Ducoulombier said. 
Officials said the baby's was a girl, but did not disclose the cause of death. 
</P>
<P>
Last week, three live babies were found abandoned in Los Angeles and Orange 
counties. They have been placed in foster care while authorities attempt to 
locate their parents. 
</P>
</TEXT>
