CALIFORNIA IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
CALIFORNIA; 
</P>
<P>
TWO QUAKES STRIKE, BUT NO HARM DONE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Moderate earthquakes struck the Hollister area of Central California and the 
Coachella Valley in Southern California, but no damage or injuries were 
reported. The Hollister quake measured magnitude 4.1 and was centered in an 
area 13 miles south-southeast of town, the U.S. Geological Survey in Menlo Park 
said. The Coachella Valley temblor was magnitude 4.2 and was centered nine 
miles east-northeast of the city of Indio, said a spokesman for the Caltech 
Seismology Center in Pasadena. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
