<TEXT>
<P>
Xavier McDaniel of the Seattle SuperSonics and Charles Oakley of the New York 
Knicks were each suspended for one game and fined $7,500 by the NBA for their 
fight last week at Madison Square Garden. 
</P>
<P>
In addition, 13 players on the Knicks and SuperSonics received automatic $500 
fines for leaving their benches during the brawl. 
</P>
<P>
McDaniel and Oakley got into a pushing match that escalated into a fight with 
5:22 left in Saturday night's game. 
</P>
</TEXT>
