</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Congresswoman Intervenes on Air Force Plan: The Air Force's secret plan to move 
the Ballistic Systems Division out of San Bernardino, which was disclosed in a 
Times story last month, has not been well received on Capitol Hill. Rep. Pat 
Schroeder (D-Colo.), chairwoman of the House subcommittee on military 
installations and facilities, has sent a letter to Air Force Secretary Donald 
Rice warning that the service lacks the authority to make the move. Schroeder 
also termed as "irresponsible" an Air Force memorandum that laid out a legal 
argument to get around a law requiring the division to stay at its current 
location. 
</P>
