</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mattel to Acquire Corgi Toys: The Hawthorne company said it will acquire Corgi 
Toys Ltd., a British concern that produces miniature cars and models, for an 
undisclosed price. The announcement comes two weeks after Mattel, which will 
sell more than $1 billion worth of toys this year, reported strong revenue for 
the Christmas season with a continuation of 1989's 25% sales growth. Corgi has 
annual revenue of about $20 million. 
