<P>
SEC Creates International Affairs Office: Securities and Exchange Commission 
Chairman Richard C. Breeden said Monday that he is creating an Office of 
International Affairs to coordinate enforcement cooperation with foreign stock 
regulators. Breeden said the new office, which will be responsible for 
negotiating formal cooperation agreements, known as memoranda of understanding, 
"underlines the very high priority the commission places on international 
cooperation." 
</P>
