</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sears Moves to Revamp Image: Sears, Roebuck &amp; Co. is ending its 10-year 
association with model Cheryl Tiegs and loosening its ties to Walt Disney Co. 
as the giant retailer continues its search for a winning image to revitalize 
its lackluster retail business. The moves come as the Chicago-based retailer 
struggles to maintain its No. 1 sales status against challengers K mart Corp. 
and Wal-Mart Stores Inc. Sears suffers from a weak fashion image, analysts say, 
because the retailer is better known to consumers as a purveyor of tools, 
appliances and automotive goods, despite a switch earlier this year to everyday 
low pricing to lure back budget-conscious shoppers of all stripes. 
</P>
