<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SAN CLEMENTE; 
</P>
<P>
PUBLIC INVITED TO GROWTH DISCUSSION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Results of a yearlong growth-management study by a citizens committee that is 
recommending changes in city development policies is being discussed at a 
Planning Commission public hearing tonight. 
</P>
<P>
Topics reviewed by the nine-person Growth Management Committee were emergency 
medical response, open space, schools, sewers, roads, water, libraries, 
parking, police and a new civic center. 
</P>
<P>
Commissioners last month were introduced to the study and continued a public 
hearing until tonight. The 7 p.m. meeting at City Hall will be televised live 
on Dimension Cable Channel 3 and will be rebroadcast at 9 a.m. and noon 
Saturday. 
</P>
