<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEVADA LAS VEGAS DOWN TO 6 CANDIDATES FOR FOOTBALL JOB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LAS VEGAS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nevada Las Vegas, which hopes to name its new football coach by the end of the 
week, had its field of candidates drop from seven to six Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Artie Gigantino, special teams coach for the Rams, was interviewed Monday by 
the 17-member committee. Jim Strong, offensive coordinator at Notre Dame, is 
scheduled to be interviewed today with Cal State Fullerton Coach Gene Murphy 
set for Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Portland State Coach Pokey Allen withdrew his name because he believed there 
weren't enough players on scholarship to rebuild the team quickly enough, 
Athletic Director Brad Rothermel said. The other three candidates are John 
Jenkins, offensive coordinator at the University of Houston, Fresno State 
recruiting coordinator Pat Hill and Gary Darnell, interim head coach at 
Florida. 
</P>
</TEXT>
