<DATELINE>
<P>
MADRID 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Four seamen were missing Monday after a Spanish freighter ran aground and sank 
in heavy seas off northwest Spain, maritime officials said. The other seven 
crew members of the 1,454-ton Baitin were rescued. 
</P>
<P>
The freighter reportedly ran aground after its cargo of salt shifted. 
