<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Shauna Snow, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pauley's Exit at 'Today': Jane Pauley's last day as co-host on "Today" will be 
Friday, Dec. 29. The early-morning show is planning an on-air tribute to 
Pauley, but details still need to be worked out. Deborah Norville takes over in 
the job Jan. 8, and, for the interim week, NBC is bringing on several former 
"Today" hosts to share the couch with Bryant Gumbel. Tom Brokaw, who was host 
of "Today" when Pauley joined the show in 1976, will join Hugh Downs and 
sportscaster Joe Garagiola as fill-in co-hosts. Shauna Snow 
</P>
