<P>
STATE INSURANCE AGENCY URGED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The sponsor of the Proposition 103 insurance initiative today said it would try 
to put a measure on the November, 1990, ballot that would create a state 
insurance agency to replace private auto insurers. 
</P>
<P>
Voter Revolt's proposed California Auto Plan would kick in if industry 
insurance averages show by Sept. 1, 1991, that rates have not been reduced to 
20% below 1987 levels and if more than 15% of motorists are uninsured. 
</P>
<P>
"Our message to the insurance companies is, 'Obey Prop. 103 or we're going to 
kick your butts out of the state of California,' " Voter Revolt chief Harvey 
Rosenfield said at a morning news conference. 
</P>
</TEXT>
