NAKED ATTEMPT AT BONN BREAK-IN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BONN 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A naked man charged through the streets of Bonn today and was shot and wounded 
in the leg when he tried to force his way into U.S. Ambassador Vernon A. 
Walters' residence. 
</P>
<P>
Police said the unnamed 25-year-old Senegalese-born Frenchman lost his temper 
after an argument with his West German girlfriend. He peeled off his clothes 
and ran through the streets in daylight. 
</P>
<P>
After unsuccessfully trying to rob an old woman, the man climbed over a wall 
into Walters' garden. His way was blocked by a guard as he ran up the steps to 
the residence and he was shot in the leg during a struggle. 
</P>
